&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;HASTINGS EARLY INTERVENTION IN PSYCHOSIS SERVICE.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Early Intervention in Psychosis Practitioner Band 5 - Full Time post.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Main area: &lt;/strong&gt;Mental Health&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Grade: &lt;/strong&gt;NHS AfC: Band 5&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Contract: &lt;/strong&gt;Permanent&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Hours: &lt;/strong&gt;37.5&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Site: &lt;/strong&gt;Cavendish House/ Bexhill Health Centre&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Town: &lt;/strong&gt;Hastings&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Salary: &lt;/strong&gt;Band 5 pay scale&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Closing Date: &lt;/strong&gt;19/01/2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Hastings Early Intervention for Psychosis is a diverse team of talented individuals, offering a wide range of specialisms. We are looking for a highly motivated qualified person (Nurse, Occupational Therapist or Social Worker) to join our team. This is a diverse and challenging role which requires an enthusiastic and dedicated person.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will work with the team manager and clinical colleagues in order to develop and co-ordinate an effective pathway of recovery for a large caseload of service users, families and carers. You will be creating collaboratively, treatment plans for people with complex presentations whilst working as part of a multi-disciplinary team.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;You will be providing a range of specialist assessments and psychosocial interventions in a variety of settings in a style that crosses traditional professional boundaries.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will have previous health or social care experience working with clients with mental health problems, and a real commitment to the principles of EIP and this client group. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;You will also have roles in developing the service, as we work to meet new Access and Wait Time Targets, including provision to ‘At Risk Mental State’ and over-35s groups. You will also be promoting the service to partner agencies and providing educational initiatives as part of broader mental health promotion to reduce stigma around psychosis. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;You will be supported by the Team Leader, the existing team, and through clinical and managerial supervision and training. We offer a commitment to support your continued professional development.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name Norman Lusted&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Job title Team Leader&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email address norman.lusted@sussexpartnership.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Telephone number 01424 726500&lt;/p&gt;
